#X text 74 128 Besides using delay lines \, let's remember about the
convolution tecnhique \, which is also used to model reverbs. We've
also seen that it can act as a general filter \, but this is only to
say filters and reverbs are intertwined concepts., f 64;
#X text 74 192 Convolution depends on Impulse Responses that capture
the reverberation or colloration model of a space. It's easy to find
"IR" sound file libraries for convolution reverbs out there. If you
have one \, you got yourself a convolution reverb in Pd. Otherwise
you can still record an IR from your bathroom or something. The example
below uses an IR of a church., f 64;
